{"id": "art-young-va-068", "type": "fact", "statement": "Young V&A, formerly the Bethnal Green Museum of Childhood, is a national museum in London that opened in 1872.", "explanation": "Originally a branch of the Victoria and Albert Museum, it became dedicated to childhood-related collections in 1974. The museum was rebranded as Young V&A in 2023 with a focus on creativity, play, and design for young audiences. Its iron-and-glass building was originally part of the 1857 South Kensington Museum.", "wowFactor": "London's oldest surviving prefabricated iron building now houses a museum designed entirely for children's creativity!", "quizQuestion": "In what year did the museum now known as Young V&A originally open?", "correctAnswer": "1872", "distractors": [{"text": "1870", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "1880", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "1860", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "1875", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "1868", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "1885", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "1874", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "1869", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "When did the Bethnal Green museum first open?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "1872", "distractors": ["1870", "1880", "1860"]}, {"question": "What was Young V&A previously called?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Bethnal Green Museum of Childhood", "distractors": ["Tate Kids", "British Children's Museum", "Royal Museum of Youth"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT true about Young V&A?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "It was built in 2023", "distractors": ["It opened in 1872", "It is in Bethnal Green", "It is a V&A branch"]}, {"question": "Young V&A is located in _____ Green, London.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Bethnal", "distractors": ["Forest", "Primrose", "Kennington"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 6, "visualDescription": "Victorian iron-and-glass museum building with colorful banners. Children playing wit