{"id": "art-sarehole-mill-070", "type": "fact", "statement": "Sarehole Mill is a historic water mill on the River Cole in Birmingham, England, and was a childhood haunt of J.R.R. Tolkien.", "explanation": "The mill dates back to at least the 18th century and is one of only two surviving water mills in Birmingham. Young Tolkien lived nearby from 1896 to 1900, and the rural setting inspired elements of the Shire in The Lord of the Rings. The mill is now a museum celebrating both its industrial heritage and literary connections.", "wowFactor": "The peaceful water mill that inspired Tolkien's Shire still stands and grinds grain in Birmingham!", "quizQuestion": "Which famous author was inspired by Sarehole Mill as a child?", "correctAnswer": "J.R.R. Tolkien", "distractors": [{"text": "C.S. Lewis", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Charles Dickens", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "William Shakespeare", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Arthur Conan Doyle", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Roald Dahl", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "George Orwell", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "H.G. Wells", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Rudyard Kipling", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "Where is Sarehole Mill located?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Birmingham, England", "distractors": ["London", "Oxford", "Manchester"]}, {"question": "Which mill inspired elements of The Shire in Lord of the Rings?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Sarehole Mill", "distractors": ["Windmill Hill", "Cotswold Mill", "Avon Mill"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT true about Sarehole Mill?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "It is in Oxford", "distractors": ["It inspired Tolkien", "It is on the River Cole", "It is a water mill"]}, {"question": "Sarehole Mill is on the River _____ in Birmingham.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Cole", "distractors": ["Avon", "Thames", "Severn"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 9, "visualDescription