{"id": "art-rumelihisari-101", "type": "fact", "statement": "Rumelihisarı is an Ottoman fortress on the European side of the Bosphorus in Istanbul, built in just four months in 1452.", "explanation": "Sultan Mehmed II ordered the fortress built at the narrowest point of the Bosphorus to control naval traffic and prepare for the conquest of Constantinople. Three massive towers were each assigned to a different vizier to ensure rapid construction. The fortress worked in tandem with Anadoluhisarı on the Asian shore to form a chokepoint nicknamed the 'Throat Cutter.'", "wowFactor": "A sultan built this fortress in just four months to strangle Constantinople's supply lines before conquering it!", "quizQuestion": "How long did it take to build Rumelihisarı?", "correctAnswer": "Four months", "distractors": [{"text": "One year", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Two years", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Six months", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Three months", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Eight months", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Five months", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Sixteen weeks", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "One hundred days", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which sultan ordered Rumelihisarı built?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Mehmed II", "distractors": ["Suleiman I", "Bayezid II", "Selim I"]}, {"question": "Which Istanbul fortress was built to control the Bosphorus?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Rumelihisarı", "distractors": ["Yedikule", "Galata Tower", "Topkapi"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT true about Rumelihisarı?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "It took two years to build", "distractors": ["It has three towers", "It faces Anadoluhisarı", "It controlled the Bosphorus"]}, {"question": "Rumelihisarı was built in _____ to prepare for Constantinople's conquest.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "1452", "distractors": ["1453", "1450", "1460"]}, {"question"