{"id": "art-villa-medici-careggi-108", "type": "fact", "statement": "The Villa Medici at Careggi near Florence was where Lorenzo de' Medici died in 1492 and hosted the famous Platonic Academy.", "explanation": "Originally a medieval farmhouse, it was transformed into an elegant villa by Michelozzo for Cosimo de' Medici in 1459. The villa became the meeting place for the Platonic Academy, where Renaissance thinkers like Marsilio Ficino and Pico della Mirandola debated philosophy. It is considered one of the birthplaces of Renaissance humanism.", "wowFactor": "The very villa where Renaissance humanism was born through philosophical debates is still standing near Florence!", "quizQuestion": "Which famous academy met at Villa Medici at Careggi?", "correctAnswer": "Platonic Academy", "distractors": [{"text": "Academy of Fine Arts", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Academy of Sciences", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Music Academy", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Aristotelian Academy", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Academy of Drawing", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Neoplatonic School", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Accademia della Crusca", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Accademia dei Lincei", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which architect transformed the villa for Cosimo de' Medici?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Michelozzo", "distractors": ["Brunelleschi", "Alberti", "Bramante"]}, {"question": "Where did Lorenzo de' Medici die?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Villa Medici at Careggi", "distractors": ["Palazzo Medici", "Palazzo Pitti", "Villa di Castello"]}, {"question": "Which philosopher did NOT attend the Platonic Academy?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Machiavelli", "distractors": ["Marsilio Ficino", "Pico della Mirandola", "Cosimo de' Medici"]}, {"question": "Lorenzo de' Medici died at the villa in _____.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "1492", "distractors": ["1