{"id": "art-galleria-continua-109", "type": "fact", "statement": "Galleria Continua in San Gimignano, Tuscany, is a contemporary art gallery housed in a former medieval cinema and theater.", "explanation": "Founded in 1990, the gallery has expanded to locations in Beijing, Les Moulins (France), Havana, Rome, São Paulo, and Dubai. It exhibits works by internationally renowned artists including Ai Weiwei, Anish Kapoor, and Michelangelo Pistoletto. The San Gimignano location creates a striking dialogue between medieval architecture and cutting-edge contemporary art.", "wowFactor": "A medieval Tuscan hill town famous for its towers now hosts one of the world's most globally connected art galleries!", "quizQuestion": "In which Tuscan town is Galleria Continua's original location?", "correctAnswer": "San Gimignano", "distractors": [{"text": "Florence", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Siena", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Pisa", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Lucca", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Volterra", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Arezzo", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Montepulciano", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Cortona", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "When was Galleria Continua founded?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "1990", "distractors": ["1985", "1995", "2000"]}, {"question": "Which gallery has locations in San Gimignano, Beijing, and Havana?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Galleria Continua", "distractors": ["Gagosian", "White Cube", "Pace Gallery"]}, {"question": "Which artist has NOT exhibited at Galleria Continua?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Banksy", "distractors": ["Ai Weiwei", "Anish Kapoor", "Michelangelo Pistoletto"]}, {"question": "Galleria Continua is housed in a former medieval _____.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "cinema", "distractors": ["church", "barn", "school"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 7, "visualDescription": "Medieval stone b