{"id": "art-dankwarderode-111", "type": "fact", "statement": "Dankwarderode Castle in Braunschweig, Germany, is a reconstructed Romanesque palace originally built by Henry the Lion around 1175.", "explanation": "The castle was the residence of Henry the Lion, one of the most powerful medieval German princes. In front of the castle stands a bronze lion statue, the oldest surviving large bronze sculpture north of the Alps, cast around 1166. The castle now houses a branch of the Herzog Anton Ulrich Museum displaying medieval art and artifacts.", "wowFactor": "The oldest large bronze sculpture north of the Alps — a lion cast in 1166 — still guards this German castle!", "quizQuestion": "Who originally built Dankwarderode Castle?", "correctAnswer": "Henry the Lion", "distractors": [{"text": "Frederick Barbarossa", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Charlemagne", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Otto the Great", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Albert the Bear", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Welf IV", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Lothar III", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Henry the Proud", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Henry the Black", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "In which German city is Dankwarderode Castle?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Braunschweig", "distractors": ["Hamburg", "Hannover", "Bremen"]}, {"question": "Which castle has the oldest large bronze sculpture north of the Alps?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Dankwarderode Castle", "distractors": ["Wartburg Castle", "Heidelberg Castle", "Nuremberg Castle"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT associated with Dankwarderode Castle?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Renaissance gardens", "distractors": ["Bronze lion statue", "Henry the Lion", "Medieval art museum"]}, {"question": "The bronze lion was cast around _____.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "1166", "distractors": ["1200", "1100", "1250"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funSco