{"id": "art-kachikally-112", "type": "fact", "statement": "The Kachikally Museum and Crocodile Pool in Bakau, The Gambia, is a sacred site where Nile crocodiles are believed to bring fertility.", "explanation": "The pool is home to over 80 Nile crocodiles that are considered sacred by the local Bojang family who have served as custodians for centuries. Women seeking fertility visit the pool to bathe in its waters, and visitors can safely touch the remarkably docile crocodiles. The adjacent museum documents Gambian history, traditional medicine, and the cultural significance of the sacred pool.", "wowFactor": "Visitors can safely touch sacred crocodiles believed to grant fertility at this remarkable Gambian pool and museum!", "quizQuestion": "In which Gambian town is the Kachikally Crocodile Pool?", "correctAnswer": "Bakau", "distractors": [{"text": "Banjul", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Serekunda", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Dakar", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Brikama", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Farafenni", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Janjanbureh", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Kololi", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Sukuta", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "What type of crocodiles live in the Kachikally Pool?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Nile crocodiles", "distractors": ["Saltwater crocodiles", "American alligators", "Dwarf crocodiles"]}, {"question": "Which Gambian sacred pool is associated with fertility?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Kachikally", "distractors": ["Folonko", "Berending", "Kartong"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT associated with Kachikally?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Venomous snakes", "distractors": ["Sacred crocodiles", "Fertility rituals", "Gambian history museum"]}, {"question": "The Kachikally pool has over _____ crocodiles.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "80", "distractors": ["20", "200", "50"]}, {"question": "The cro